Update 2022 (February):

After 2 years of the Covid19 pandemic, and different approaches by different countries, I’m please to say that Wittenborg has stayed on track, even with recurring restrictions and lockdowns. 2021 saw more new students, 380, starting at our business school than ever before, with over 1200 students registered during the year. Last year, we saw 175 bachelor, master and MBA graduates go forward to the next exciting stage of their careers.

I’m optimistic and can see an exciting year ahead, and I think that in this respect 2022 will bring us a much brighter and more relaxed year, with less focus on what trouble COVID-19 is causing us and more emphasis on other important matters – including many of the issues covered by the Sustainable Development Goals, that Wittenborg has committed to encompassing in its curriculum, including those covering the environment, but also peace, justice and strong institutions (#SDG16). Wittenborg’s values of #Internationalisation, #Diversity and #Ethics will remain the centre of support for the school’s mission in 2022.

Some of our highlights for 2022:
•	2022 – a continued quest for quality higher education and applied research;
•	Making the Strategic Plan happen in 2022;
•	The Big October Event: EuroChrie 2022 Conference;
•	Saying Hello to our new location:  Brinklaan and say goodbye to Aventus in 2022;

#Wittenborg35: Save the Date: 11th November, 2022 – Wittenborg 35 Celebration Gala
